text: Finally going to get surgery on my foot. My point is if you ever are in pain and the doctor tells you are not don’t think your crazy. Keep looking until you find a good doctor. I’m so excited to get my foot finally fixed.

author: Jenapher B
text: Bone I jacked up when I fell. I had some of those doctors tell me I was imagining this pain in my foot!  I started to wonder if I was going crazy until finally I found 1 good doctor who figured it out. Thousands of dollars later and over a year walking with pain and I’m

author: Jenapher B
text: Going from doctor to doctor I’m finally having foot surgery in a few weeks to shave the bone spurs down and relocate the nerve that was dislocated when I fell. He will do that with the first surgery then the next surgery will be the bone fusion surgery to fix the

author: Jenapher B
text: He couldn’t believe that the podiatrist I had gone to last year didn’t see the large bone spurs on the x-rays. He completely must have been blind not to see the bone spurs or just wanted to bill my insurance for a foot brace and sent me on my way. After an entire year of

author: Jenapher B
text: Every single one of these doctors could not figure out why I had so much pain in my left foot so all they did was give me a prescription. Out of all these doctors just 1 figured out what is wrong with my foot.

author: Jenapher B
text: Long story short I have been to my general doctor twice, a knee doctor 3 times, a neurologist 4 times and had an EMG (nerve shock test), an Orthopedic spine doctor, a Rheumatologist and 2 Podiatrists. I’ve had a MRI done on my foot/ankle, knee, lower and upper spine.

author: Jenapher B
text: I fell on 1/8/2021 while walking my dogs & blood was pouring from my knee but I managed to get back to my house with my dogs. Took a shower and bandaged my knee and off to work I went. After about 2 weeks I finally went to my doctor to see what could be done.
